 1985- cohort arranged in three files: a numerator file (linked records of live births and infant deaths), a denominator plus file (live birth records offered as numerator/denominator data sets to facilitate computation of infant mortality rates), and an unlinked file (infant death records which cannot be linked to a corresponding birth record).  aSystem requirements: Fully IBM-compatible microcomputer 286/386/486; 640K memory, 5 megabytes free space on a hard drive in the installation directory and another 6 megabytes of space for temporary files; MS-DOS 3.1 or higher; Microsoft CD-ROM extensions, version 2.0 or higher; fully installed CD-ROM reader, printer is recommended.  aLatest issue consulted: 1991. 0aInfantsxMortalityzUnited StatesxStatisticsvDatabases. 0aChildbirthzUnited StatesvStatisticsvDatabases. 0aUnited StatesvStatistics, MedicalvDatabases. 0aUnited StatesvStatistics, VitalvDatabases. 7aChildbirth.2fast0(OCoLC)fst00854780 7aInfantsxMortalityxStatistics.2fast0(OCoLC)fst00972171 7aUnited States.2fast0(OCoLC)fst012041551https://id.oclc.org/worldcat/entity/E39PBJtxgQXMWqmjMjjwXRHgrq 7aDatabases.2fast0(OCoLC)fst01411643 7aStatistics.2fast0(OCoLC)fst01423727 7aMedical statistics.2fast0(OCoLC)fst01423729 7aVital statistics.2fast0(OCoLC)fst01423730 7aDatabases.2lcgft 7aStatistics.2lcgft 7aVital statistics.2lcgft2 aNational Center for Health Statistics (U.S.)1https://id.oclc.org/worldcat/entity/E39QQPVp7WHXJqdQ7gXTYbFQkt 0aNCHS CD-ROM.nSeries 20.  aC0bGPO  abc31 20260313  aCONSERCHANGEDb2026031302961cas a2200541 a 00046476120260326090422.0m     q  d f      co ug|||||||||961113d1994199udcuar   qs   f0    0eng c  a98643396zsn 96034737  a78626425a1008451421a1049022334a13362950489 aocm35906562  a(OCoLC)35906562z(OCoLC)78626425z(OCoLC)1008451421z(OCoLC)1049022334z(OCoLC)1336295048  aOLAbengcOLAdIULdDLCdOCLdDLCdGPOdIULdOCLCQdDLCdOCLCQdOCLCFdOCLCQdOCLCL